node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.title: How Porsche went from sports cars to SUVs ... and EVs

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.text: Violence and mass shootings erupted over the weekend, and could continue. 274 mass shootings have occurred this year, with 304 dead, which is on pace for one of the most violent years in history. Here's what the country's outlook is.

node.title: Violence and mass shootings erupted over the weekend

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Mark Zuckerberg thinks Facebook will profit by building a "metaverse' CNBC'.

node.text:
It’s either the next evolution of the internet or the latest corporate buzzword to get investors excited over some nebulous innovation that may not even come to pass over the next decade.⁠
⁠
Either way, tech companies — primarily Facebook — are increasingly boosting the concept of the “metaverse,” the classic sci-fi term for a virtual world you can live, work and play inside. If you’ve seen the movie “Ready Player One,” you have a pretty good idea of what the metaverse is: Strap on a set of computerized glasses, and you’re transported into a digital universe where anything is possible.⁠
⁠
How does Facebook plan to profit off of CEO Mark Zuckerberg's vision to pivot Facebook from a social media company to a metaverse company in the coming years? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, car and text that says 'Grand jury indicts Trevor Milton, founder of electric carmaker Nikola, on three counts of fraud CNBC NIKOLA'.

node.text:
A federal grand jury charged Nikola founder Trevor Milton with three counts of criminal fraud for lying about “nearly all aspects of the business” to bolster stock sales of the electric vehicle start-up, according to an indictment unsealed Thursday.⁠
⁠
The U.S. Attorney’s Office in Manhattan accused the 39-year-old billionaire, who resigned as chairman in September, with two counts of securities fraud, including making false statements about the company, and wire fraud.⁠
⁠
Details on how the indictment impacted Nikola stock at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'u.S. GDP increased at 6.5% pace in the second quarter, well below expectations அမய CNBC'.

node.text:
The U.S. economy rose at a disappointing rate in the second quarter –– a sign that the U.S. has escaped the shackles of the Covid-19 pandemic, but still has more work to do.⁠
⁠
GDP accelerated 6.5% on an annualized basis. That was slightly better than the 6.3% gain in the first quarter, which was revised down narrowly. While that would have been strong prior to the pandemic, the gain was considerably less than the 8.4% Dow Jones estimate.⁠
⁠
Even though GDP rose at a weaker rate than expected in Q2, it's likely to be the high point of the pandemic recovery. Read why at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '"The only people who are not vaccinated are just a--holes." Charles Barkley CNBC'.

node.text:
“Yes, I’m vaccinated,” says NBA legend Charles Barkley. “Everybody should be vaccinated. Period.”⁠
⁠
The 58-year-old NBA Hall-of-Famer says he personally thinks sports leagues should force players to get vaccinated: “Can you imagine if one of these guys that are not vaccinated, if they get one of these players’ kids, wives, girlfriends, moms and dads sick and they die over some unnecessary conspiracy bulls---,” Barkley says. “I think that would be tragic.”⁠
⁠
Details on how many NFL, MLB and NBA players reportedly have gotten at least one shot at the link in bio. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 28, 2021. May be an image of ‎phone, body of water and ‎text that says '‎New Nokia smartphone is a "military grade" model with 5G that can take a beating NOKI ن CNBC‎'‎‎.

node.text:
HMD Global says the Nokia XR20 is the most durable phone it’s created to date. 💪⁠
⁠
The maker of Nokia-branded phones debuted a slew of new devices Tuesday, including a “military grade” smartphone designed to withstand intense environmental conditions. The XR20 sports a tough 6.67-inch Gorilla Glass Victus display from American tech firm Corning and can resist damage from scratches and drops from about 6 feet, the company says.⁠
⁠
Details on how long the phone can be submerged in water at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Google postpones return-to-work until October, will require vaccinations CNBC'.

node.text:
Google is extending its office return for employees until Oct. 18 amid the latest Covid-19 outbreaks, says CEO Sundar Pichai.⁠
⁠
In an email to employees Wednesday, Pichai also said the company will require anyone coming to the office to be vaccinated, beginning in the U.S. in coming weeks.⁠
⁠
Details on how Google plans to eventually bring its workers back to the office at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Biden will require federal workers to get the Covid vaccine or submit to testing INTED STA 1 CNBC'.

node.text:
🚨 BREAKING. 🚨⁠
⁠
President Joe Biden this week is expected to announce his administration will require federal workers to be vaccinated for the coronavirus or else submit to strict testing measures, NBC News reported Wednesday.⁠
⁠
Biden is set to unveil the new rules, which followed a White House internal policy review, during a speech Thursday, two administration officials told NBC.⁠
⁠
This story is developing. Get full updates at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
In an effort to help curb soaring student loan debts, Walmart announced Tuesday it will pay 100% of college tuition and book costs for its associates, starting Aug. 16.⁠
⁠
About 1.5 million part-time and full-time associates of Walmart and its Sam’s Club subsidiary will be eligible to learn new skills and earn college degrees, the company said.⁠
⁠
Get full details at the link in bio. 👀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Apple demolishes earnings expectations with iPhone sales surging nearly 50% CNBC'.

node.text:
Apple reported strong fiscal third-quarter earnings on Tuesday, demolishing Wall Street expectations. Every one of Apple's major product lines grew over 12% on an annual basis. 🔥⁠
⁠
Overall, Apple's sales were up 36% from the June quarter last year. iPhone sales increased nearly 50% on an annual basis. ⁠
⁠
Full details on how Apple performed vs. Wall Street's expectations at the link in bio. (With @Fang)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and text that says 'CDC to reverse indoor mask policy to recommend them for fully vaccinated people in Covid hot spots CNBC'.

node.text:
🚨 BREAKING. 🚨⁠
⁠
The CDC is expected to recommend Tuesday that fully vaccinated people begin wearing masks indoors again in places with high Covid-19 transmission rates, according to people familiar with the matter.⁠
⁠
Federal health officials still believe fully vaccinated individuals represent a very small amount of transmission, according to the sources. Still, some vaccinated people could be carrying higher levels of the virus than previously understood and potentially transmit the virus to others, they said.⁠
⁠
Full details: Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Olympic champ Simone Biles out of team finals with medical issue, says USA Gymnastics CNBC'.

node.text:
Simone Biles is out of the team finals.⁠
⁠
The Olympic gymnastics champ left the competition floor with the team doctor after her vault. USA Gymnastics said in a statement she “will be assessed daily to determine medical clearance for future competitions.”⁠
⁠
Get the developing details at the link in bio.
